":"NDC","status":"Archived","category":"Energy efficiency","purpose":"Promote vehicle improvements","instrument":"Inspection and maintenance","asi":["Improve"],"quote":"In Qatar, Vehicles Inspection Services regulates the emissions of vehicles.","page":null,"modes":[],"geography":[],"measure_status":null},{"doc_id":17705,"document":"First Generation NDC","version":"NDC 1.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Archived","category":"Energy efficiency","purpose":"Promote vehicle improvements","instrument":"General vehicle improvement measures","asi":["Improve"],"quote":"Qatar continues to improve the emission standards for new motor vehicles, in accordance with regional and global emission standards.","page":null,"modes":[],"geography":[],"measure_status":null},{"doc_id":21704,"document":"Second Generation NDC","version":"NDC 2.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Archived","category":"Mode shift and demand management","purpose":"Public transport improvement","instrument":"General public transport improvement","asi":["Shift"],"quote":"The Doha Metro and Lusail Tram are major milestones in the development of public transportation and subsequent reduction of emissions from this sector.","page":6,"modes":["Transit rail"],"geography":["Urban"],"measure_status":null},{"doc_id":21704,"document":"Second Generation NDC","version":"NDC 2.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Archived","category":"Aviation and maritime","purpose":"Promote improvements in aviation","instrument":"Airport CO2 certification","asi":["Improve"],"quote":"The level 3 accreditation status for Hamad International Airport is another major initiative towards sustainability.","page":6,"modes":["Aviation"],"geography":[],"measure_status":null},{"doc_id":21704,"document":"Second Generation NDC","version":"NDC 2.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Archived","category":"Electrification","purpose":"Promote electric mobility","instrument":"General e-mobility measures","asi":["Improve"],"quote":"The country has also taken significant strides to adopt electrification of on-road vehicles by committing to electrify its public transport system","page":6,"modes":["Road","Bus"],"geography":[],"measure_status":null},{"doc_id":21704,"document":"Second Generation NDC","version":"NDC 2.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Archived","category":"Electrification","purpose":"Promote electric mobility","instrument":"EV charging infrastructure measures","asi":["Improve"],"quote":"investing in installation of charging infrastructure across the country.","page":6,"modes":[],"geography":[],"measure_status":null},{"doc_id":82665,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","category":"Aviation and maritime","purpose":"Promote improvements in shipping","instrument":"General shipping improvement","asi":["Shift"],"quote":"In terms of waterborne transport modes, Qatar aims to develop a continuous passenger ferry service between Hamad Port and Doha Port, with several intermediate stations.","page":11,"modes":["Water"],"geography":[],"measure_status":"Planned"},{"doc_id":82665,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","category":"Aviation and maritime","purpose":"Promote improvements in shipping","instrument":"General shipping improvement","asi":["Improve"],"quote":"LNG Vessel Program. The LNG Vessel Program to increase LNG export capabilities is focused on modernizing existing fleets with advanced vessels designed for higher operational efficiency. The vessels are equipped with dual-fuel systems that will utilize LNG as the primary fuel, hence, lowering emissions compared to the use of conventional bunker fuels. Efforts to optimize fuel consumption further include deploying advanced hull designs, air lubrication systems, and underwater coatings.","page":12,"modes":["Water"],"geography":[],"measure_status":"Planned"},{"doc_id":82665,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","category":"Mode shift and demand management","purpose":"Public transport improvement","instrument":"General public transport improvement","asi":["Shift"],"quote":"Development of Public Transport Infrastructure. The shift to public transport and non-motorized modes of transport is a key component of reducing GHG emissions from land transport. The provision of high-quality, affordable public transport options is key to incentivizing a shif in transport mode choices. Public transport in Qatar continues to provide passengers with multiple options and is facilitating multi-modal connections.","page":11,"modes":["Active mobility","Bus","Transit rail"],"geography":[],"measure_status":"Planned"},{"doc_id":82665,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","category":"Mode shift and demand management","purpose":"Public transport improvement","instrument":"Public transport integration and expansion","asi":["Shift"],"quote":"The current Doha Metro network is expected to see extensions to existing metro lines, as well as a new Light Rail scheme connecting within and to Lusail New Town.","page":11,"modes":["Transit rail"],"geography":["Urban"],"measure_status":"Planned"},{"doc_id":82665,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","category":"Mode shift and demand management","purpose":"Public transport improvement","instrument":"BRT","asi":["Shift"],"quote":"Rail transport in Doha is complemented by an integrated, extensive Bus Rapid Transit (BRT) system. The BRT network will be further expanded with additional bus routes, providing alternative, lower-cost options for key corridors, improving local accessibility to workplaces, and incentivizing the use of public transport buses over private vehicles.","page":11,"modes":["Bus"],"geography":["Urban"],"measure_status":"Planned"},{"doc_id":82665,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","category":"Transport system improvements","purpose":"Improve infrastructure","instrument":"Expansion of infrastructure","asi":["Shift"],"quote":"At the regional level, Qatar’s future public transport development plans are expected to include the implementation of a Long-Distance & Regional Rail Network by 2030.","page":11,"modes":["Rail"],"geography":["Inter-city"],"measure_status":"Planned"},{"doc_id":82665,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","category":"Electrification","purpose":"Promote electric mobility","instrument":"General e-mobility measures","asi":["Shift","Improve"],"quote":"Electrification of Public Transport & Taxis. Qatar aims to maximize the use of electric urban transit buses and plans to transition its traditional taxi fleet to hybrid, plug-in hybrid, and electric vehicles to reduce emissions.","page":11,"modes":["Taxis","Bus","Transit rail"],"geography":["Urban"],"measure_status":"Planned"},{"doc_id":82665,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","category":"Alternative fuels","purpose":"Promote alternative fuels","instrument":"General renewable energy support measures","asi":["Shift","Improve"],"quote":"Renewable Energy Generation for Public Buses. In 2022, the Lusail Bus terminal – the world's largest electric bus depot with a capacity of 478 buses - was equipped with 11,000 PV solar panels that generate 4 MWh of electricity per day.","page":11,"modes":["Bus"],"geography":["Urban"],"measure_status":"Planned"},{"doc_id":82665,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","category":"Electrification","purpose":"Promote electric mobility","instrument":"EV charging infrastructure measures","asi":["Improve"],"quote":"Deployment of EV charging infrastructure. To address one of the main barriers to the adoption of electric vehicles (EVs) by private car buyers, Qatar is significantly expanding its network of public EV chargers. To improve EV charging convenience, a user-friendly smartphone app has been developed, enabling users to locate charging stations, check availability, initiate charging sessions, and track energy usage.","page":11,"modes":["Cars"],"geography":[],"measure_status":"Planned"},{"doc_id":82665,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","category":"Energy efficiency","purpose":"Promote vehicle improvements","instrument":"General vehicle improvement measures","asi":["Improve"],"quote":"Improving Standards. Qatar aims to establish various standards and requirements for road transportation, addressing all new light-duty vehicles and heavy-duty vehicles.","page":12,"modes":["Road","Cars","Truck"],"geography":[],"measure_status":"Planned"},{"doc_id":82665,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","category":"Alternative fuels","purpose":"Promote alternative fuels","instrument":"LPG/CNG/LNG support measures","asi":["Improve"],"quote":"LNG Vessel Program. The LNG Vessel Program to increase LNG export capabilities is focused on modernizing existing fleets with advanced vessels designed for higher operational efficiency. The vessels are equipped with dual-fuel systems that will utilize LNG as the primary fuel, hence, lowering emissions compared to the use of conventional bunker fuels. Efforts to optimize fuel consumption further include deploying advanced hull designs, air lubrication systems, and underwater coatings.","page":12,"modes":["Water"],"geography":[],"measure_status":"Planned"}],"adaptation":[{"doc_id":21704,"document":"Second Generation NDC","version":"NDC 2.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Archived","category":"Structural and Technical","measure":"Transport System Adaptation","quote":"The State of Qatar has undertaken/planned several projects to enhance the overall infrastructure in \nthe country with a strong focus on sustainability. Besides the sustainable stadiums being developed \nfor the FIFA World Cup 2022, several other projects such as the Qatar integrated rail project, \nexpressway program, roads and drainage program, development of sustainable residential complexes \n(Lusail city, Msheireb downtown), development of parking bays, inter alia hold key to Qatar’s plans \nof sustainable infrastructure development.","page":10,"modes":["Road","Rail","Water"]},{"doc_id":82665,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","category":"Structural and Technical","measure":"Resilient transport technologies","quote":"Qatar is promoting the integration of renewable energy sources, such as solar power. These efforts are complemented by investments in electric vehicle infrastructure, Tarsheed code, district cooling systems, and digital monitoring platforms, all of which contribute to reducing emissions, optimizing energy use, and enhancing the resilience of the energy sector to climate-related risks.","page":20,"modes":[]},{"doc_id":82665,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","category":"Structural and Technical","measure":"Resilient transport technologies","quote":"Sustainable Transport and Mobility: Supports climate-resilient mobility by piloting autonomous vehicles, transitioning taxi fleets to low-emission vehicles,","page":22,"modes":["Taxis"]},{"doc_id":82665,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","doc_type":"NDC","status":"Active","category":"Structural and Technical","measure":"Risk assessment","quote":"studying climate risks to transport infrastructure, such as metro networks.","page":22,"modes":["Transit rail"]}],"benefits":[{"doc_id":82665,"document":"Third Generation NDC","version":"NDC 3.0","status":"Active","type":"Economic benefits","quote":"The plan aims to create an integrated, efficient, and sustainable transportation network that not only meets the mobility needs of Qatar's population but also contributes to the nation's broader goals of sustainability, economic diversification, and enhanced quality of life.","page":11}],"references":[],"asi_summary":{"Shift":7,"Improve":6},"category_summary":{"Mode shift and demand management":3,"Aviation and maritime":2,"Electrification":2,"Alternative fuels":2,"Transport system improvements":1,"Energy efficiency":1},"target_years":[{"year":2040,"scope":"economy-wide"}],"btr":{"available":false,"documents":[],"measures":[]},"links":{"changing_transport_search":"https://changing-transport.org/?s=Qatar","tdc_search":"https://portal.transport-data.org/search?country=QA"},"publications":[{"title":"Ten Years of Turning Plans into Movement","url":"https://changing-transport.org/ten-years-of-turning-plans-into-movement/","date":"2026-04-27","type":"Article","scope":"global"},{"title":"How Can Transport Systems Become More Gender-Responsive?","url":"https://changing-transport.org/how-can-transport-systems-become-more-gender-responsive/","date":"2026-03-13","type":"Article","scope":"global"},{"title":"Is Transport on Track for 1.5°C?","url":"https://changing-transport.org/publications/is-transport-on-track-for-1-5-degrees/","date":"2026-02-24","type":"Publication","scope":"global"},{"title":"When Open Data Works","url":"https://changing-transport.org/when-open-data-works/","date":"2026-01-30","type":"Article","scope":"global"},{"title":"The Stony Path from Ambition to Implementation","url":"https://changing-transport.org/the-stony-path-from-ambition-to-implementation/","date":"2025-11-23","type":"Article","scope":"global"},{"title":"How to Distinguish CO2 and other Emission Standards","url":"https://changing-transport.org/publications/how-to-distinguish-co2-and-other-emission-standards/","date":"2025-11-05","type":"Publication","scope":"global"},{"title":"Time to be Accountable at Transport and Climate Change Week","url":"https://changing-transport.org/time-to-be-accountable-at-transport-and-climate-change-week/","date":"2025-10-02","type":"Article","scope":"global"},{"title":"